@GRMIDX{{index="@HI{{you ni naru}}" grammar="@HI{{you ni naru}}"}}

<body>

<h1>@HI{{you ni naru}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vru{{}} @EM{{@HI{{you ni naru}}}}
<li> @Vnai{{}} @EM{{@HI{{you ni naru}}}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
These sentence patterns indicate a change from one state into another. The verbs used express possibility or ability
(for example, potential verbs).
</p>

<p>
The form which uses @Vru{{}} means that something which could not be done now can be done. The form with
@Vnai{{}} indicates that something which previously could be done can now no longer be done.
</p>

<p>
The form @EM{{@HI{{you ni natteiru}}}} emphasises that the current state has come about after a long process.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{yatto @KJ{{oneself^revolve^car}}ni @KJ{{ride}}reru@EM{{you ni}} narimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I've finally become able to ride a bicycle.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

